						<div class="postbody">To me, ClearType looks beautiful. It resembles the printed word much more than Windows 3.1-era 1-bit rendering ever did. One problem I have specifically with GDI ClearType, not so much with other subpixel rendering implementations, is that Helvetica's 'm', 'n', and 'r' aren't hinted for the extreme stretching that GDI ClearType applies to letters. I can post samples if you want.</div>

